Morocco,Q3s8L_fjHjU,UgzwcjtTwosk3dQ_R454AaABAg,,@AidanaGalym,"My experience in Marrakesh was quite mixed.
On one hand, the city is vibrant and full of character. But unfortunately, the negatives were too noticeable for me.
The Marrakesh Medina and the markets feel extremely chaotic. The streets are very narrow and crowded, yet at the same time filled with motorcycles, carts, and even donkeys. It often feels unsafe and stressful to walk there as a pedestrian.

I was also very concerned about hygiene. Meat is often displayed openly without proper refrigeration, which does not look safe and immediately affects your appetite and trust in the food.

In general, the city did not feel very clean. There are unpleasant smells in many areas, especially in the old town, and the air can feel heavy at times.
The food may not be for everyone. It contains a lot of spices, and sweet ingredients like raisins are often added to savory dishes. Personally, I found it difficult to enjoy these flavors, especially after seeing how food is handled.
Prices in many places also felt quite high considering the overall level of comfort.
Overall, Marrakesh is a unique experience, but it’s definitely not for everyone. It’s better to come prepared for these aspects of the city.",2026-04-22T06:09:53Z,2026-04-22T06:09:53Z,1,False,1.0,2026-05-12T02:01:18.027648
