Casablanca,t2jBSAWCg5s,UgzJI8bjKOH3rCjrzS14AaABAg,,@odysseusrex5908,"This is the greatest movie ever made. It is infinitely quotable and infinitely quoted.
The reason Rick was refusing to give them the letters was not that he wanted to keep Ilsa close to him but that he wanted to punish her for seemingly betraying him.
I think you missed what Louis was doing. He was using his position of power to force young women to sleep with him in return for exit visas. That is what he was doing with the young Bulgarian girl. What she wanted to know from Rick was whether Louis would actually give her and her husband their visas if she gave him what he wanted. Rick tells her he always has, but then goes and makes sure they get the money they need so their can be no doubt.
When Louis tells his men to round up the usual suspects, of course he knows who just shot Major Strasser tight in front of his eyes. He wants to cover up that fact and protect his friend. Also, he has just, finally, picked a side. You saw him open and then throw away a bottle of Vichy water. Vichy is a resort town in France known for its mineral springs. It was also the de facto capital of France after the government fled Paris. Throwing away the bottle represented his break with the Vichy government and decision to join the continuing fight against the Nazis.",2026-05-04T16:42:43Z,2026-05-04T16:42:43Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-12T02:01:38.841915
