Casablanca,t2jBSAWCg5s,Ugz353UBhhFN1mwgs3B4AaABAg,,@MobiusMinded,"What I love about Casablanca. It’s the perfect example of the art and craft of Hollywood cinema reaching its apex. It wasn’t necessarily meant to be great. It was a convoluted, ever changing, almost at the edge of disaster during production. There are in fact many Hollywood films that beat it in many categories…. But the sheer heart of it. The result of all those actors, the crew, the writing, production and direction; fighting every day to make something. All those craftsmen and filmmaker’s, at the height of their powers, finally making something that was not only greater than the sum of of parts, but timeless. When it was released it did so so, but time has shown the diamond that toiled in the rough. …that, plus this song always makes me cry..",2026-05-03T00:35:36Z,2026-05-03T00:55:10Z,2,False,0.0,2026-05-12T02:01:38.842364
