Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgygZU6QQK-K6GiPyIt4AaABAg.AI8sQf1RvHxAJMGJclXMzv,UgygZU6QQK-K6GiPyIt4AaABAg,@cdeleo9336,@tims7639planning to go there will you share contacts of your guide,2025-06-14T15:49:27Z,2025-06-14T15:49:27Z,0,True,,2026-05-12T02:02:12.235960
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgygZU6QQK-K6GiPyIt4AaABAg.AI8sQf1RvHxAJcg20wZ10Q,UgygZU6QQK-K6GiPyIt4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,Hi @cdeleo9336: TimS used the same tour as we did. Here's the link: https://www.airbnb.com/experiences/604421 —Judy,2025-06-21T10:10:04Z,2025-06-21T10:10:04Z,0,True,,2026-05-12T02:02:12.235978
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,Ugwm-74gikWd5EmR78l4AaABAg.AHLlqV6Pq1XAHNERjUGT4q,Ugwm-74gikWd5EmR78l4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"Hi Muhammed, We LOVE London. In fact our daughter was just there two days ago after visiting with us in Malta! May will be a nice time to visit Marrakech. The weather is hot but not unbearable, especially if you avoid the hottest parts of the day. And May is a month of celebrations. The Kelaa M'Gouna or Festival of the Rose runs from May 5-9 if you will be around to attend that. Have a terrific time! —Judy",2025-04-26T07:49:32Z,2025-04-26T07:49:32Z,0,True,,2026-05-12T02:02:12.403119
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgxuUUq3xrtcndmn-Kx4AaABAg.AH93pO8FVUiAHDeSgIl9_t,UgxuUUq3xrtcndmn-Kx4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"Hi Laura, The culture in Morocco is more modest, so if you want to respect the local culture, you won't wear clothes that are too revealing. I'm wearing tank tops, and my skirts are close to knee length, but you could cover your arms with an airy blouse and wear loose long pants or long skirts. I wasn't going to go out and buy these items since we're full time travelers, but I tried to be as modest as possible given my limited wardrobe. Morocco is reasonably understanding of tourists and don't necessarily expect them to follow all the Muslim customs. Personally, I wouldn't wear crop tops or show off my stomach or my full back or wear a bathing suit top (although we saw all of these by tourists). Does this help at all? —Judy",2025-04-22T14:33:11Z,2025-04-22T14:33:11Z,0,True,,2026-05-12T02:02:12.587105
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgyjBXrRN4434_OtEkp4AaABAg.AH6JcS9XcqKAHDUnluogM_,UgyjBXrRN4434_OtEkp4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"Hi Angela, There are no required vaccinations that the Moroccan government checks to see if you have had. However, with the monkeys in the Sahara, it wouldn't be the worst thing to have a rabies vaccination (we do not have that vaccination). We made sure that we had Hepatitis A, B, tetanus, MMR (measles, mumps, and rubella), typhoid, and cholera before we traveled to Egypt. If you have any specific concerns, it's not a bad idea to check with a travel doctor who can give you recommendations. But specific to Morocco? Nothing is required for entry. —Judy
🎥 Why we got vaccinated in Rome before heading to Egypt: https://youtu.be/ZJG4MI76u58
