Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgyjBXrRN4434_OtEkp4AaABAg.AH6JcS9XcqKAHDXfrhFZHe,UgyjBXrRN4434_OtEkp4AaABAg,@Roathcourt,@ thank you so much Angela,2025-04-22T13:25:13Z,2025-04-22T13:25:13Z,0,True,,2026-05-12T02:02:12.736631
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,Ugzgj9tbOmptG1mUAcV4AaABAg.AGx6eqm664_AGx71udc2kW,Ugzgj9tbOmptG1mUAcV4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"We loved our time in Morocco! We especially enjoyed Fes, but we spent a month between Marrakech, the Sahara Desert, and Fes. We would definitely like to spend time exploring more of the country. —Judy",2025-04-15T19:05:21Z,2025-04-15T19:05:21Z,0,True,,2026-05-12T02:02:12.926694
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,Ugz1GttXKozX0cZhDqx4AaABAg.AGsAZLPMU1UAGsBwyFqJ6j,Ugz1GttXKozX0cZhDqx4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"Hi Syed, You will always be at the mercy of the border agent who you talk to. Offhand, I don't recall that they asked us anything. We may have had to show proof of onward travel afterwards and possibly the address of our riad where we were staying, but nothing else. These are common questions we get asked occasionally, but I think every agent does their own thing. It can also be dependent on your passport, and we are Americans. That's not to say in these unusual times that border agents will continue to be as kind to us. —Judy",2025-04-13T21:12:01Z,2025-04-13T21:12:01Z,0,True,,2026-05-12T02:02:13.089203
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgzVBKkk_fCKCGEPjxl4AaABAg.AGXs4tM4mb3AGYDb2MBC3R,UgzVBKkk_fCKCGEPjxl4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"Hi Thelminetta, Neither of us recalls that we had to do that. Of course, you're always at the mercy of the specific passport security personnel you end up getting and possibly also your passport. You might enjoy our other episodes from our 40+ days in Morocco. —Judy
