Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgzVBKkk_fCKCGEPjxl4AaABAg.AGXs4tM4mb3AGYH2U3AXCU,UgzVBKkk_fCKCGEPjxl4AaABAg,@thelminettas8694,"Thank you! I find your vlogs very informative. I avoid those that don’t teach - how to get to and from a destination, best location for accomodation, transportation, etc. My husband and I started traveling more and thought Marrakech and Fes are interesting cities to explore after Portugal and Spain in the fall. Thank you! I’m a subscriber now.",2025-04-05T18:12:33Z,2025-04-05T18:12:33Z,1,True,,2026-05-12T02:02:13.267449
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgzVBKkk_fCKCGEPjxl4AaABAg.AGXs4tM4mb3AGYhQuTvl7z,UgzVBKkk_fCKCGEPjxl4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"We are so flattered. Thank you very much! You are right about Morocco being a perfect complement to those countries. We've been to Madrid and Barcelona, but people mentioned that Granada is a great place to visit before or after Morocco because there are certain similarities. After the Moors were expelled from Spain, many of them settled in Marrakech. Likewise certain North African dynasties once ruled parts of Spain, including Granada. We hope you have a great time! —Judy",2025-04-05T22:11:49Z,2025-04-05T22:11:49Z,0,True,,2026-05-12T02:02:13.267455
