🎥 Morocco Travel Series: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLNT98lWfwdF0_pL4S2LnqlBz2KBX9XMCc",2025-02-06T22:32:27Z,2025-02-06T22:32:27Z,0,True,,2026-05-12T02:02:14.077072
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgxgTojif_sIweHMebp4AaABAg.AE3KIek4Gb0AEAYfRHrC1D,UgxgTojif_sIweHMebp4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"It's hard for us to not be able to record in certain places, which is why we might opt to skip them. We'd rather put our budget on places we can more easily share with our viewers. Of course, there are times when it's worth it to us, but it's so much easier when they do allow photographs. We use Airbnb quite a bit, but especially in Fes, our riad served us a very hearty breakfast every day and we were really able to save a lot of money not having to chase down an extra meal every day. Our Marrakech location wasn't ideal and although breakfast was cheap, arranging it was a bit confusing, so we only ate in once. Thanks for sharing your experience! —Judy",2025-02-05T20:02:00Z,2025-02-05T20:02:00Z,0,True,,2026-05-12T02:02:14.207022
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgyIVqczQ0iOrKhcO6l4AaABAg.ADlWeBG9LiQADlwbogMWm2,UgyIVqczQ0iOrKhcO6l4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"We don't shop for souvenirs as full-time travelers with no home base, but we are glad to hear you enjoyed this trio of museums. We will have to come back and check them out. We were in the Atlas Mountains, but again we skipped some of the shopping. Thanks for the recommendation about Dar Zite. We have a full series from our 40+ days in Marrakech if you're interested in watching. It's linked below. —Judy
