Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgxP0tL_F3KdY6w_WEh4AaABAg.ABX29zpLxeHABXMUn44R3-,UgxP0tL_F3KdY6w_WEh4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"@jmw0368 Sorry, that's a man's name 😉 —Judy",2024-12-02T03:03:54Z,2024-12-02T03:03:54Z,0,True,,2026-05-12T02:02:16.217329
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgwbKLgbNvwSEPGeYXt4AaABAg.ABL2HbKxK5aABLdOl6RLcm,UgwbKLgbNvwSEPGeYXt4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"Hi @juanmonge7418, It's an overnight train from Tangier to Marrakech. But it looks like it makes other trips as well. The experience is very mixed. Here are some reviews about it on TripAdvisor. We didn't take it ourselves, so we can't offer any personal opinions. If you go, we'd love to know what you think! https://www.tripadvisor.com/Attraction_Review-g293734-d318065-Reviews-Marrakesh_Express-Marrakech_Marrakech_Safi.html —Judy",2024-11-27T13:49:29Z,2024-11-27T13:49:29Z,0,True,,2026-05-12T02:02:16.362132
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,Ugx_uGmjXey5dDUuYeN4AaABAg.ABKSonVD4xDABKVD0lKkQr,Ugx_uGmjXey5dDUuYeN4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"Hi @TranLe-vy5nz, People are friendly, but we suggest you don't take directions unless you are truly lost. Personally, we avoided some of the street food and stuck to restaurants because we didn't trust that our stomachs could handle it. Don't take pictures of people without their permission; I'd also plan to stick to the main streets of the Medina. It is easy to get lost and you might not want that to happen in the more remote passageways. We found Moroccans to be very kind and helpful, but crime can happen anywhere. We have many more suggestions in our Do's and Don'ts for Morocco, which is linked below in our full series from Marrakech.

We hope you have a great time! —Judy
