All of your burden, all your sorrow
Turn it off until tomorrow, but today
We’re gonna be okay

All the mean things your head tells you, forget it
The pressure people give you, forget it
The love, the hate, the pleasure, pain
They matter not right now so
Close your eyes and feel the rhythm, surrender
And let your body start to take over
Our hearts in sync, don't care what people think
The floor is ours to take 

One step forward one step back
Don't be shy and don't hold back
One step forward one step back

You've got me so damn desperate
You're all I want, no counterfeit
So just tonight, is it alright
If you could see just past the light?
Peculiarly drawn to you, this feeling somehow isn't new
I really don't know what to do

Tell me, tell me pretty stranger
